cppcodec
------------------------------------------
Header-only C++11 library to encode/decode base64, base64url, base32, base32hex
and hex (a.k.a. base16) as specified in RFC 4648, plus Crockford's base32.

Runtime requirements:
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-10.2.0-1
  ninja-1.10.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tplgy/cppcodec

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tplgy/cppcodec/archive/v0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cppcodec-0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cppcodec-0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cppcodec-0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cppcodec-0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

